race.comment: The speedy SHOWLAS (4) resumes and has the form to be winning. She's won 1/2 fresh and at her only go this track/distance. She will jump and run from the inside barrier and enjoys a 3kg claim. Suited and should be ready to go. CLEANEMUP (1) will be a lot more competitive than the form line suggests. He's been racing in better class and was only beaten 2.4L at Ascot last time. The 3kg claim brings him right into it. BARECOVE ROCK (2) brings strong city form over a mile to resumption and has warmed up with a Belmont trial hitout. May need one but he has some talent and maps to advantage. RANYX (3) also resumes and just missed in a recent Belmont trial. He's fast and can give a sight.
